  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Distribution of Winterization Assistance to Vulnerable Families</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The 2021-2022 Joint Winterization strategy highlights high needs over the winter season in Afghanistan. This will be critical as many - particularly internally displaced persons and returnees who reside in open spaces or in congested informal settlements - are left in poor, unhygienic and undignified living conditions with little access to basic services. This project is focused on the provision of cash-for-winterization, cash-for-non-food items, and in-kind distributions (winter clothing and blanket) in six provinces to 2,300 internally displaced families and other vulnerable groups in Afghanistan.</narrative>
  </description>
